# CODEOWNERS — auto-assigns reviewers for PRs touching protected paths.
#
# Lines are matched in order; the last matching pattern wins. See:
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Replace @<team> with the GitHub team slug that owns the path. Until that
# team exists, leave a placeholder so the file is syntactically valid but
# GitHub auto-review-request is a no-op.

# Default — everything not matched below.
*                              @claude-base-maintainers

# High-impact paths — affect every downstream consumer. Require owner approval.
/policy/                       @claude-base-maintainers
/scripts/                      @claude-base-maintainers
/.github/                      @claude-base-maintainers
/.claude-plugin/               @claude-base-maintainers
/plugins/base-tools/hooks/     @claude-base-maintainers
/LICENSE                       @claude-base-maintainers
/CONTRIBUTING.md               @claude-base-maintainers
# Linking contract — see LINKED_REPOS.md. Changes here MUST land in both sibling repos.
/LINKED_REPOS.md               @claude-base-maintainers
/.github/workflows/sync-to-sibling.yml      @claude-base-maintainers
/.github/workflows/verify-sibling-sync.yml  @claude-base-maintainers
